\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Put the rational numbers in a sequence 
\begin_inset Formula $r_{0},r_{1},r_{2},r_{3},\cdots$
\end_inset

 such that 
\begin_inset Formula $r_{0}=0$
\end_inset

.
 We divide the real line into countably many non-overlapping intervals.
 Specifically, let 
\begin_inset Formula $A_{0}=[0,1]$
\end_inset

, 
\begin_inset Formula $A_{1}=[-1,0]$
\end_inset

, 
\begin_inset Formula $A_{2}=[1,2]$
\end_inset

, etc (see the following figure).
